==English==
===Etymology===
From [[Greek]] [[γεωκεντρικός]] (''geokentrikos'') "having the earth as his centre", from [[Ancient Greek]] [[γαία]] (''gaia'') "earth" + [[κέντρον]] (''kentron'') "centre".
===Adjective===
'''geocentric''' (''absolute; no comparative or superlative'')

#Having the Earth at the center. Usually in reference to the [[Solar System]].

====Antonyms====
*[[heliocentric]]

